I"Œ<p>In physics, the fundamental dimensions are mass, length, and time, which are measured in kilograms [kg], meters [m], and seconds [s], respectively. These units are known as the SystÃ¨me Internationale (SI) units, or International System, and they are what we will be utilizing for the most of this course. However, the Centimeterâ€“Gramâ€“Second (CGS) System and the British Engineering (BE) System are two alternative systems of measurement that are still in use (refer to the table below).</p>

