<hr />
<p><strong>Example 1.</strong> Express the mass of 375,000,000,000 g in: <br />
    a. Gg <br />
    b. Mg <br />
    c. Tg</p>

\[\begin{align*}
	\text{Mass}&amp;=375,000,000,000 \text{ g} \\
			&amp;= 375 \times 10^9 \text{g}	&amp;&amp; \text{move the decimal point 9 places to the left} \\
			&amp;= 375 \text{ Gg}	&amp;&amp; \text{replace $10^9$ with the symbol ``G"}
\end{align*}\]

<p>Hence, 375,000,000,000 g = 375 Gg</p>

